9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 130, L.D. 280, “An Act to Establish
10 Lifetime Ferry Passes for Retired Maine State Ferry Service Employees”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4408 is enacted to read:
14 §4408. Lifetime ferry passes for retired ferry service employees
15 A former state employee who is receiving retirement benefits after at least 15 years of
16 employment with the Maine State Ferry Service and who is a year-round resident of one of
17 the served islands of the Maine State Ferry Service is eligible to receive a lifetime ferry
18 pass and a waiver from any reservation fees if the lifetime ferry pass is presented when
19 making the reservation. For the purposes of this section, "lifetime ferry pass" means a
20 nontransferable pass that provides on a ferry operated by the Maine State Ferry Service:
21 1. Walk-on passage. Unlimited walk-on passage for a passenger to and from the
22 island on which the retiree resides; and
23 2. Passenger and vehicle passage. One round-trip passage per month for a passenger
24 and that passenger's vehicle during peak season as determined by rules adopted by the
25 Department of Transportation and 2 round-trip passages per month during off-peak season
26 as determined by rules adopted by the department. A reservation for passage described in
27 this subsection must follow rules adopted by the department. For the purposes of this
28 subsection, "vehicle" means a noncommercial motor vehicle with 4 tires or fewer and an
29 overall length of 20 feet or less.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment specifies that a former state employee who was employed for at least
3344 15 years with the Maine State Ferry Service and who is a year-round resident of an island
